INSERT INTO "fio_juvenile" VALUES ('FC25001847','2025-04-23 19:30','151766','Coppinger, Joseph','JAMES MOORE','MORTON ST','DORCHESTER','MA','02124','NULL','Stopped','Reasonable Suspicion','NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'Body Worn Camera, Juvenile','Subject Stop ofXXXXX/XX/XXXXat XXXMorton Street.  The weather on this date was approximately 70 Degrees Fahrenheit.  Officers observed an individual wearing a black winter jacket, black sweatshirt, and a black shiesty style ski mask walking on Morton Street towards Norfolk Street with his hands in his pockets firmly grasping the inner layer of clothing. The individual took note of officers and continued to look over his shoulder keeping an eye on the officers as the travelled down Morton Street. Officers conducted a U-turn and observed this individual continuing in the direction of officers. As officers exited the cruiser and approached the individual they observed a large bulge in his front right pocket.   Officers stopped the individual and conducted a pat frisk of his person which yielded negative results.   This individual was identified asXXX(DOB: XX/XX/XXXX FIO''D and released  C111F (Coppinger/Cox)',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-23','19:30',2025,4,23);
INSERT INTO "fio_juvenile" VALUES ('FC25002011','2025-05-01 18:30','153099','FULLAM, PATRICK','CARL BLANDO','FREDERICK ST','SOUTH BOSTON','MA','02127','NULL','Stopped','Reasonable Suspicion','NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'Juvenile, Body Worn Camera','Officers responded to a radio call for B&E atXXXXXSt. Caller described two young, thin build black males, one wearing a red hoodie and one wearing a blue hoodie outside ofXXXXXattempting to climb in the second story window. Officers observed XXXXX and XXX outside the entrance toXXXXXwearing red and blue hoodies respectively. XXXstated they were just horsing around jumping from one railing to another. Officers did not observe any signs of forced entry to any units. Both parties were advised they were trespassing on BHA property and released from scene.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-01','18:30',2025,5,1);
INSERT INTO "fio_juvenile" VALUES ('FC25002023','2025-05-02 00:49','168362','O''Neill, Matthew','JAMES MOORE','RIVER ST','MATTAPAN','MA','02126','NULL','Stopped','Probable Cause','NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'Gun, Body Worn Camera, Juvenile','1:00am 05/02/25  Radio call for two males Trespassing at XXXRiver Street, Boston.  Officers observed two males exiting the building matching the description given by the caller.  Suspect #1 - XXX XX/XX/XXXX- F/A''s, Armed Robbery masked, B&E on BOP. After a brief foot chase XXX discarded a firearm from his waistband and was placed under arrest.  Suspect #2 made good on his escape but was later positively identified through body worn camera asXXX XX/XX/XXXX- F/A''s, B&E, Larceny of M/V on BOP.  C113A (O''Neill/Williamson)',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-02','00:49',2025,5,2);
INSERT INTO "fio_juvenile" VALUES ('FC25002041','2025-05-02 19:16','168389','Byrnes, Patrick','TIMOTHY COUGHLIN','NULL','BOSTON','MA','02128','NULL','Stopped','Reasonable Suspicion','NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'School, Juvenile, Body Worn Camera','Officers responded to R/C for "Person with a Gun" at Central Square and Liverpool Street in East Boston. Officers were informed via BPD Operations Channel 2 that 5 juveniles in a grey Nissan were shooting people with BB guns. Operations reported that the Nissan fled down Liverpool Street towards Maverick Square.  Officers located MA XXX(grey 2016 Nissan Rogue SUV) occupied by 5 juvenile aged parties at the intersection of Maverick and Border Street. Upon approaching the vehicle, officers observed several Nerf "Gel Fire" blasters in plain view. Officers gave exit orders and began removing the Nissan''s occupants. They were identified as-  XXX (DOB XX/XX/XXXXDriverXXX(DOB XX/XX/XXXXFront Passenger Side XXX(DOB XX/XX/XXXXRear Driver Side XXX (DOB XX/XX/XXXXRear Middle SeaXXXDOB XX/XX/XXXXRear Passenger Side Seat  All parties were pat frisked with negative findings and placed into handcuffs. Officers explained to the parties that they were being detained. After the parties were removed, officers observed 2 bottles of "Orbeez" gel balls sitting in plain view. An additional 2 bags of "Orbeez" gel balls were located in the Nissan''s center console. A CJIS inquiry showed all parties to be negative for warrants.   Officers requested that BPD Operations Channel 2 contact the calling party to determine whether there was an identified victim. Operations made contact with the calling party, who stated that they were hit by a gel ball but did not wish to talk to police or have any further involvement.   Officers determined that all involved parties, with the exception of XXXwere juveniles. XXXmother, the registered owner of the Nissan, took custody of the Nissan and stated that he no longer had permission to operate it. XXXwas released from the scene. All other parties were transported back to District A7 where they were released to their respective parents  FIOE to associate parties with each other and with "Orbeez" related incidents, which usually pick up in the warmer weather.  -G101F (Byrnes, P./Agudelo)',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-02','19:16',2025,5,2);
INSERT INTO "fio_juvenile" VALUES ('FC25002232','2025-05-10 00:00','144325','KENNEDY, DALE','PATRICK MORRISON','GENEVA AVE','DORCHESTER','MA','02122','NULL','Stopped','Encounter','NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'Juvenile, Body Worn Camera','About 4:20 PM, Saturday, May 10, 2025, Officer D. Kennedy (H436F) responded to XXXGeneva Ave (Target) where the subject XXX) was stopped by Target Loss Prevention for shoplifting. XXXmother XXX came and picked up XXXfrom the store. XXXwas trespassed from Target for a year, until 05/10/2026. Target did not want to pursue charges. XXXsaid XXXis diagnosed with autism.  FIO Completed to document.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-10','00:00',2025,5,10);
INSERT INTO "fio_juvenile" VALUES ('FC25002256','2025-05-11 03:23','106745','DIAZ, JOSE','RAFAEL RODRIGUEZ','WALNUT AVE','ROXBURY','MA','02119','NULL','Stopped','Reasonable Suspicion','NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'Body Worn Camera, Juvenile','PO Jose M Diaz Jr (106745) BT55A at 3:27AM on Sunday 5/11/2025 outside XXXWalnut Ave. Roxbury BWC activated.  911 call for the following outside XXXKensington Park Roxbury;   * 05/11/25 03:23:48 (pct14): CALLER STATES GROUP OF TEENAGERS WITH GUNS SHOOTING A MUSIC VIDEO  * 05/11/25 03:23:58 (pct14): CALLER STATES THEY WERE FLASHING THEM AT A CAMERA  * 05/11/25 03:24:09 (pct14): STATES ABOUT 6 MALES  * 05/11/25 03:24:20 (pct14): STATES ALL BLACK MALES, WEARING DARK CLOTHING  * 05/11/25 03:24:31 (pct14): ONE HAS ON PURPLE HAT  * 05/11/25 03:24:41 (pct14): CALLER KEEPS DISCONNECTING CALL.  * 05/11/25 03:24:53 (pct14): UNK DIRECTION OF FLIGHT  Officer Diaz (BT55A) heard units broadcast that the group of teens had fled in different directions upon arrival. Units on scene were requesting assistance in setting up a perimeter at the foot path outlets throughout Warren Gardens spanning outward from the Kensington Park cul-de-sac, including Dale St. Fenno St. Saint Richard St. Warren St. and Walnut Ave.  Officer Diaz approached up Walnut Ave. from Warren St. and observed a police car on Walnut Ave. just past Fenno St. at the base of a parking lot driveway. Officer Diaz heading in that direction observed Officer Flores (BK01A) and Officer Dominick (B432A) off with two individuals outside of XXXWalnut Ave. As he parked the police car, Officer Diaz observed Officer Dominick in a struggle with the male party she was detaining. Due to the distance between Officer Diaz and the struggling Officer and Subject, Officer Diaz raised his voice to get the subject''s attention and told him he could be "tased" while drawing (1:26/37:16), arming (1:27/37:16), and activating the warning feature (1:27/37:16) of the "Taser10" electronic energy weapon as a distraction and de-escalation method to give Officer Dominic a more immediate assistance while Officer Diaz closed the gap. During this time, Officers Reynolds and Kimaiyo (B103A) arrived from behind a fence and the Subject was guided to the ground and placed in handcuffs, detained, and later identified as XXX. At no time was the Taser10 discharged and Officer Diaz re-holstered immediately when the Officers gained control of the Subject and detained him. Throughout this interaction, a voice could be heard emitting from the "Ring" doorbell camera associated with XXXWalnut Ave. The Officer reassured the resident they were conducting a police investigation and would be away from her front door as soon as reasonably possible. Officer Diaz later transported the second detained individual (XXX, 12 y/o) along with Officer Kimaiyo (B103A) bringing XXX back to XXXKensington Park. All above actions were captured via Body Worn Camera (BWC). FIOE generated to document the use of the Taser10 as a de-escalation tactic.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-11','03:23',2025,5,11);
INSERT INTO "fio_juvenile" VALUES ('FC25002292','2025-05-13 11:00','40006646','Resil, Jacob','LUCAS TAXTER','POLK STREET','CHARLESTOWN','MA','02129','15','Encountered','Intel','NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'Juvenile','On 5/13/2025, at 11am, Housing Officers were patrolling the Bunker Hill Development when they observed two juveniles walking through the development by XXXCarney Court. The two juveniles spotted the officers and then halted their movement in that direction. Both juveniles waited for officers to leave the area.  Officer Resil then went up to the juveniles to have an encounter with them, but they ignored the officer and continued to walk and took a left onto Polk Street. Officer Resil followed both individuals who then proceeded to take another left into the courtyard of XXXPolk St all while looking back at the officer several times. It is to be noted, that both individuals seemed to be walking aimlessly in the development. Officer Resil was able to catch up with the individuals and asked if they lived in the development and both individuals said "no".  Officer Resil then asked for both individuals to identify themselves with one giving the name of XXXXX/XX/XXXXand the other giving the name of XXX(DOB: XX/XX/XXXXXXXand XXXexplained to officers that they were waiting for a friend to give XXXback his keys for his apartment. Officer Resil advised both that they were not to be loitering in the development. MK43 yielded an address for XXXat XXXRuggles Street, Roxbury and XXXwith the address of XXXNorth Ave, Dorchester.   FIO for identification and information purposes.   Z428/Z436 (Resil/Sotunbo)',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-05-13','11:00',2025,5,13);
INSERT INTO "fio_juvenile" VALUES ('FC25002295','2025-04-29 18:09','153137','TURNER, MATTHEW','JAMES MOORE','MORTON ST & WILDWOOD ST','BOSTON','MA','02126','NULL','Stopped','Intel','NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'Juvenile, Body Worn Camera','Officers conducted subject stop on XXXXX/XX/XXXXand another juvenile male identified only as XXXat Morton St. and Wildwood St. Officers first observed the two male parties on Blue Hill Ave. passing Landor St. when they abruptly stopped and appeared to hide behind a vehicle upon seeing Officers. Officers observed that the first male XXXclosely resembled a BOLO from a person with a gun incident from B2.   As Officers turned onto Morton St. they observed the two males start walking again. Officers looped the block and as they turned onto Morton St. a few minutes later, observed the two males again, who upon seeing them turned onto Wildwood St. Officers drove past them and then exited their cruiser in order to speak to them at which time they observed the males had already turned around and were walking back towards Morton St.   Officers eventually caught up to the two males and conducted a pat frisk of XXXperson for weapons due to his behavior, to no avail. XXXmother appeared on scene and began complaining to the Officers regarding the stop at which time they explained the reasoning for it. During the conversation XXXmother made comments about them living at XXXBlue Hill Ave.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-29','18:09',2025,4,29);
