INSERT INTO "fio_juvenile" VALUES ('FC25002779','2025-06-01 19:42','113288','Jimenez, Cindy','ALLISON ENG','NULL','EAST BOSTON','MA','02128','NULL','Encountered','Encounter','NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'Juvenile, Other Agency/Unit Notified','Officer Jimenez received a call for a missing juvenile found in Massport park by Brooks and Bremen Street. Juvenile was identified asXXXmissing out of Everett since May 10, 2025.  EMS transported Ms. XXXto MGH for evaluation. Everett PD notified along with DCF.   Ms. XXXstated that she was staying in East Boston and was safe. Would not disclose location. Also stated to have been with her current boyfriend, XXXwho resides on Putnam Street but is currently in DYS custody due to a recent arrest in Winthrop, MA.   FIO for future encounters.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-01','19:42',2025,6,1);
INSERT INTO "fio_juvenile" VALUES ('FC25002837','2025-06-03 16:25','168499','Cavaco, Cedric','CHARLES MOORE','BENNINGTON ST','EAST BOSTON','MA','02128','NULL','Stopped','Reasonable Suspicion','NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'Body Worn Camera, Juvenile','Officers were on bike patrol riding through Day Sq, East Boston, while they were flagged down by an individual, who requested to remain anonymous for an assault. That individual stated that three individuals just assaulted another male then took off running down towards Putnam Street, East Boston. Two other unidentified individuals also flagged officers down stating 3 males, 2 with facemasks wearing all black and a 3rd individual wearing black pants. Officers witnessed 3 individuals matching the description speed walking away from officers and as officers approached, they refused to stop.   Suspect #1XXX (DOB XX/XX/XXXXwas wearing all black. Just graduated from Excel Academy, East Boston.  Suspect #2 XXX(DOB XX/XX/XXXXwas wearing black pants and a white t shirt with a blue facemask. Attends East Boston High School.   Suspect #3 XXX (DOB XX/XX/XXXXwas wearing a black hooded sweatshirt and blue sweatpants along with a black shiesty. Attends Excel Academy.   Officers PAT Frisked all suspects finding a pocketknife on suspect#3 in which he stated was for his protection. Officers confiscated the pocketknife. All suspects were released from the scene as the victim was nowhere to be found.   FIOE to Identify.   GT55F (Cavaco)',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-03','16:25',2025,6,3);
INSERT INTO "fio_juvenile" VALUES ('FC25002872','2025-06-05 01:55','151191','ASHE, KEVIN','JAMES MOORE','BLUE HILL AVE','MATTAPAN','MA','02126','NULL','Stopped','Reasonable Suspicion','NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'Juvenile, Body Worn Camera','About 1:40 AM on Thursday, 06/05/2025, Officers assigned to District B-3 conducted a subject stop in the area of XXXBlue Hill Avenue in relation to a call for an assault at XXXBlue Hill Avenue. (P250259545)  Officer stopped 3 juvenile males based on the description provided by the original caller and identified the following individuals;  S1 -XXX, DOB XX/XX/XXXXblack mask, grey hoodie, blue jeans.  S2 - XXX DOB XX/XX/XXXXblue surgical mask, black hoodie, orange shorts  S3 - XXX DOB XX/XX/XXXXblack mask, black hoodie, black jeansXXXwas determined to be reported missing out of Framingham and was transported to Boston Medical Center Pediatrics by Boston EMS, DCF notified.  XXXrefused to identify himself or provide contact information for any legal guardian. Officers were able to identify him via Mark43 and BRIC missing person flier and notified DCF.  XXXprovided a home address and number for his mother and was transported home. While in BPD custody, XXXstated that he didn''t feel the need to run from Officers because "I didn''t have my gun," and while sitting in the back seat of a cruiser, observed the Mark43 home page where a photo of XXX prompting him to say "Why you showing me that bitch ass n----, AP." XXXalso expressed his desire to "beat his ass," while awaiting transport in the district station.  C112A (Ashe/Parlon)',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-05','01:55',2025,6,5);
INSERT INTO "fio_juvenile" VALUES ('FC25002879','2025-06-05 12:48','144476','MONZON, RENZO','JOHN SHAUGHNESSY','OLD IRONSIDES WAY','CHARLESTOWN','MA','02129','NULL','Encountered','Reasonable Suspicion','NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'Juvenile','About 12:48 pm on Thursday, 06/05/25 while on patrol in the area of Medford St, Officers observed 3 males walk into the stair case of XXXOld Ironsides Way.  While maintaining observation of the three males, the Officers observed that the males were just staying in the staircase area and not going into any of the apartments. In order to insure that they werent going to trespass or loiter the Officers made contact.   While walking up the stairs, Officers observed one of the male parties immediately place an item into his pocket when he observed the Officer''s presence. To insure that a weapon wasnt just hidden the male party was immediately pat frisked to no avail. When asked if the males lived there they all stated noXXXXXXXXXX/XX/XXXXXXXXX  All parties were explained that they were trespassing and advised to move along which they did without incident.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-05','12:48',2025,6,5);
INSERT INTO "fio_juvenile" VALUES ('FC25002924','2025-06-06 11:13','140282','ADAMS, CHRISTOPHER','JAMES MOORE','NORFOLK ST','DORCHESTER','MA','02124','7','Stopped','Reasonable Suspicion','NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'Body Worn Camera, Juvenile','Officers were on patrol in the area of Norfolk Street and Wentworth Street when they observed a male walking with a group coming from Tech Boston. At that time, the temperature was 75 degrees with 70% humidity and the male was observed wearing a black puffy winter coat with the hood up, a black hooded sweatshirt underneath, black shiesty mask, and black winter hat.   Officers approached the male, identified asXXXnd explained their reasoning for the stop. No weapons were located during a frisk. XXXhad no logical explanation for his attire and stated he understood why he was stopped and why his appearance led Officers to believe he may be armed.  Adams/Harrington',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-06','11:13',2025,6,6);
INSERT INTO "fio_juvenile" VALUES ('FC25002927','2025-06-06 20:32','162960','MIllane, Brandon','MICHAEL MCCARTHY','WASHINGTON ST','DORCHESTER','MA','02124','NULL','Encountered','Reasonable Suspicion','NULL','MA','OTHER: ST FW 150',NULL,'Black',NULL,'Moped',NULL,'Body Worn Camera, Juvenile, Moped','R/C for suspicious individuals in the rear of XXXWashington St. Officers encountered the following parties: XXXPrior F/A on BOP), (XXX, and XXX. Officers observed the following clothing description on these individuals:  XXXBlack shiesty mask, black hooded sweatshirt with white "old english style" lettering across the front and back, black pants, a gray "walking boot" on right leg.   XXXBlack fitted hat with bright yellow coloring under brim, black shiesty mask, light blue surgical mask, black hooded sweatshirt, black basketball shorts.   XXXBlack winter style hat on head, Black zip up jacket/hoodie, white tee shirt, gray sweatpants.  XXXBlack shiesty mask, gray zip up hooded sweatshirt, black pants.   Officers observed four mopeds in the rear of this address. Based on officers'' observations, all parties were frisked for weapons, a silver folding knife was recovered from XXXwaistband area. Officers canvased the immediate area for weapons yielding negative results. Mopeds were frisked for weapons yielding negative results. A CJIS query of all parties revealed no active warrants. A CJIS query of moped (MA VIN XXXrevealed it was stolen by means of armed robbery (knife) on (05/10/25) by "three black males wearing ski masks" (I252037259). Based on CJIS results of moped and additional factors, XXXwas placed under arrest by officers. It should be noted XXXbecame aggressive with officers on scene and was placed in handcuffs as a result. Outstanding parties were cordial with officers.   FIO for documentation purposes, and to associate parties with this address. Millane/Mulvey (H104F).',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-06','20:32',2025,6,6);
INSERT INTO "fio_juvenile" VALUES ('FC25002935','2025-06-07 02:49','132064','O''BRIEN, SEAN L.','JOHN HUGHES','NULL','DORCHESTER','MA','02121','NULL','Stopped','Encounter','NULL','NULL','OTHER: Flywing 150',NULL,'BLUE',NULL,'Moped',NULL,'Juvenile, Body Worn Camera, Moped','Around 2:49 AM, officers encountered a male pushing a blue Scooter inbound on Blue Hill Avenue near Seaver Street following a call for shots fired in the area of Franklin Park and Walnut Park.   Officers spoke with XXX, who stated the Moped had broken down and he was pushing it home. A CJIS inquiry of the VIN XXXshowed no status. There are no reports of VIN located in Mark43. Frisk yielded negative results.  C111A (OBrien and Crush)',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-07','02:49',2025,6,7);
