INSERT INTO "fio_juvenile" VALUES ('FC25003997','2025-07-24 10:00','40009234','Barbosa, Carlos','PAUL DONLON','GENERAL LAWRENCE J LOGAN WAY','SOUTH BOSTON','MA','02127','40','Stopped','Reasonable Suspicion','NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'Juvenile, Gang','On Thursday, 07/24/2025 at approximately 10:00PM, Housing PO''s conducted a subject stop at XXXLogan Way in the Mary Ellen McCormack Development regarding information received during an ongoing firearm investigation (reference I#252048545). Officers were conducting surveillance of XXXLogan way and observed subjects known to them as XXX and XXXboth active XXXgang members, loitering outside of XXXLogan Way with a group of about 4 younger juveniles and 1 male approximately 18-23 years of age.  Throughout the duration of conducting surveillance, Officers observed a juvenile, Hispanic male approximately 14-16 years of age, wearing a black t shirt, grey shorts, and a black Nike fanny pack across his back. Officers are aware of the city-wide trend of firearms being held in fanny packs. Officers observed this unknown juvenile pin the fanny pack against his right arm numerous times and when he observed two marked Boston police cruisers drive into the development, the male quickly entered the hallway of XXXLogan Way grabbing onto the fanny pack. The male exited approximately 5 minutes later once he noticed the police presence was not for him or the group.  Due to the ongoing firearm investigation into XXXlogan way, direct resident and management complaints regarding firearm activity within the hallways and front courtyard areas of XXXlogan way, XXXand XXXhaving prior firearm history as well as being targets of this investigation, the observations made during surveillance, Officers believed this unknown juvenile was armed, specifically with a firearm.  Upon concluding surveillance and approaching the group, XXXwas now no longer with the group and the unknown juvenile male was frisked yielding negative results. The unknown juvenile male was asked if he lived there and he declined as well refusing to identify himself. The older male was confrontational at first, stating he was XXX brother however, eventually calmed down once he was explained Officer''s reasons for being there.  XXXwas cordial, even humorous with Officers, as he was making jokes, laughing, and speaking calmly with Officers.   Investigation is ongoing.  FIO for intel.  Z433 (Barbosa) Z430 (Ellsworth)',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-07-24','10:00',2025,7,24);
