INSERT INTO "fio_juvenile" VALUES ('FC25004541','2025-08-20 14:51','098663','MACPHERSON, ERIC','RAFAEL RODRIGUEZ','DACIA ST','DORCHESTER','MA','02125','NULL','Stopped','Reasonable Suspicion','NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'Juvenile, Body Worn Camera','While on patrol near the intersection of Dalkieth Street and Howard Avenue, the VK23 observed three young males gesturing towards the officers as they were driving on Howard Avenue. As the officers drove slowly toward the males, the three split up and began running away. P.O. MacPherson detained one individual dressed in all gray with a red baseball hat who refused to identify himself. P.O. Schain and BHA Sgt. Stevens pursued a second male who was ultimately caught at XXX Dacia Street with the assistance of Area B2 units. That male was identified as XXX. The third male was not located but was seen running down Balfour Street.   A search of the suspect''s flight path proved unsuccessful and the officers drove Mr. XXXback to his grandmother XXXXXXat XXX Balfour Street, apartment XXX. She informed the officers that the male who fled, as well as the male who refused to identify himself, had attempted to run into her apartment but she told them to leave. She was advised to contact the police if she found any illegal items that may have been discarded inside her residence.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-20','14:51',2025,8,20);
INSERT INTO "fio_juvenile" VALUES ('FC25004543','2025-08-20 00:00','178110','Kelley, Greg','DANIEL PUSEY','HARRISON AVE','BOSTON','MA','02118','NULL','Encountered','Reasonable Suspicion','NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'Moped, Body Worn Camera, Juvenile','About 5pm on Wednesday 08/20/2025, Officers Kelley and Tal assigned to the D101F responded to an Investigate Premise at XXXHarrison Avenue.  Upon arrival officers made contact with caller who stated there were suspicious people in the bike cage section of the lower parking garage. Caller stated there had been previous break ins and was concerned.  Officers made contact with three juveniles in the bike cage on the lower level of the above address. Two male juveniles, later identified as XXX andXXXwere observed to be actively working on a moped with a large assortment of tools. A female juvenile who identified herself asXXX stated that she lived in the building. XXXmother was contacted to confirm her apartment/residence in the building.   XXXstated he was transferring moped frames in the garage due to the inclement weather. XXXwas observed to be in the process of disassembling the entire moped. Both male subjects were cordial and polite with officers and provided information upon questioning.   CJIS query revealed negative results for all parties.  Body Worn Camera Activated.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-20','00:00',2025,8,20);
