INSERT INTO "fio_juvenile" VALUES ('FC25004704','2025-08-30 17:10','168475','Smith, Unique','JAMES MOORE','NULL','BOSTON','MA','02124','NULL','Encountered','Encounter','NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'Juvenile','About 5:10 PM on Saturday 08/30/2025, while on patrol in the area of Harvard St, Officer Smith in the C640F observed a group of 4 juveniles riding bikes in the area of Harvard St and Senator Bolling Cir.   The officer had contact with this group of juveniles earlier in the week for a previous call for aggravated assault (See I# 252070188).   From prior knowledge, the suspects who matched the description from the prior report, were given names of "XXX On today''s date the officer observed the same juveniles, with the same description. One wearing a pink sheisty mask, black tshirt, black shorts, riding a blue bike and another wearing a red sheisty mask riding a green bike, while the others were on foot.   The officer asked the juvenile with the pink sheisty if they were staying out of trouble and he stated "Nope, I''m trying to catch someone who was talking shit."   It should also be noted that while the officer was browsing reports on Mark 43, the same group of juveniles are suspects in another aggravated assault which also occurred in the last few days (see I# 252071553).',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-30','17:10',2025,8,30);
INSERT INTO "fio_juvenile" VALUES ('FC25004707','2025-08-30 18:00','40010934','Clifton, Ardie','KEITH MONAHAN','BROOKWAY RD','ROSLINDALE','MA','02131','30','Encountered','Intel','NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'Other Agency/Unit Notified, Juvenile','About 6:00 PM on Saturday, August 30, 2025, 2 juvenile victims involved in a recent incident were encountered at XXXBrookway Road, Roslindale.  The juveniles, XXX (D.O.B XX/XX/XXXXand XXX(D.O.B XX/XX/XXXXwere seen engaging in a street football game as part of a Unity Day event for the Archdale Village BHA Development. XXXapproached Officer Clifton and asked, "Do you remember me?" Officer Clifton replied he did. XXXalso asked a similar question after which both cordially greeted Officer Clifton with a handshake.  XXXwas dressed in a red hooded sweatshirt with black pants and black and white basketball style sneakers. XXXhair was in an afro similar to the day of the original incident. XXXwas dressed in all black, with his t-shirt, pants, socks and crocs all being black. XXXwas wearing a fitted black skull cap with silver framed glasses.  XXXand XXXstated they both lived within the Development but that their parents weren''t around. XXXand XXXalso declined to give an exact residential address though this information can easily be found via Officer Clifton''s access to tenant records for the property.  Both XXXand XXXstated they hadn''t had any similar issues since the original incident and have not re-encountered the suspect. Officer Clifton advised both XXXand XXXhe patrols the Development often thus they would likely see him again in the future.  Dedham Police Officer Liam McDonnell was made aware of the sighting from this evening accordingly.    Clifton (Z435)',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-30','18:00',2025,8,30);
