INSERT INTO "fio_juvenile" VALUES ('FC25004728','2025-09-01 02:00','167728','Fawkes, Joseph','JAMES MOORE','WOOLSON ST & WILDWOOD ST','MATTAPAN','MA','02126','NULL','Stopped','Probable Cause','NULL','MA','Accord',NULL,'Gray','4 Door, Sedan','Passenger Car/ Automobile',NULL,'Juvenile, Gun, Body Worn Camera','02:00 AM T-Stop of MA REG XXXat Woolson St/ Wildwood St which led to a firearm arrest ofXXX (I252072553).  Officers observed the vehicle parked in a tow zone in the area of a person shot that occurred at XXXWoolson St at 12:40 AM (I252072545). Officers also located multiple shell casings at Woolson St/Wildwood St in the immediate area of where the car was located.  Driver identified asXXX, DOB: XX/XX/XXXXFront passengerXXXDOB: XX/XX/XXXXRear right passenger XXXDOB: XX/XX/XXXXRear left passengerXXX, DOB: XX/XX/XXXX While conducting a pat-frisk, after a violent struggle Officers located a firearm in the front waistband ofXXX. Additionally, Officers located a firearm inside of a backpack behind the rear armrest with XXXs name on it. Pat frisk of XXXand XXXyielded negative results, FIO''d and released.  C112A (Fawkes/Mulrean) C431A(Williamson)',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-01','02:00',2025,9,1);
INSERT INTO "fio_juvenile" VALUES ('FC25004732','2025-09-01 15:33','178088','Perry, Tynia','RAFAEL RODRIGUEZ','MARTIN LUTHER KING JR BLVD','ROXBURY','MA','02119','NULL','Stopped','Reasonable Suspicion','NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'Juvenile, Body Worn Camera','At about 3:33pm on Monday, 09/01/25, Officers Perry and Duarte in the B103D responded to a radio call for a report of a Person with a Gun at XXXMartin Luther King Boulevard, Roxbury XXX The suspect was described as a black male, 16 years old, thin build, 5''3 wearing a black shiesty, white t-shirt, black shorts, carrying a Popeyes bag. A description of the parties that the suspect was with included three females and one male.   Upon arrival, officers observed an unknown male party matching the description of the suspect, later identified as XXXOfficers observed two female parties and one male party standing with XXXThe two female parties were identified as XXX Officers identified the male party asXXXOfficers frisked all parties and the bags in their possession with negative results.   XXXexplained to officers that he and his friends were in the store looking for a specific shoe size (size 7) for XXXXXXstated that XXXthen asked XXXfor the size, to which XXXstated that the store did not have in stock. XXXfurther stated that XXXhad an attitude and began arguing with them, telling them that they can leave the store. XXXstated that they then exited the store, but XXXcontinued to follow them outside of the store, yelling at them.   It should be noted that all parties were cooperative and provided their information and their version of the incident in a respectful manner.  Body worn cameras activated.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-01','15:33',2025,9,1);
INSERT INTO "fio_juvenile" VALUES ('FC25004734','2025-09-01 20:48','102679','D''ADDIECO, SANTINO','PATRICK CURTIN','MALCOLM X BOULEVARD','BOSTON','MA','02119','NULL','Stopped','Reasonable Suspicion','NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'NULL','NULL','NULL',NULL,'Juvenile, Body Worn Camera','YVSF  Officers were on patrol in the area of Nubian Square as an effort to address the numerous quality of life concerns including drinking in public, illegal drug distribution as well as to proactively prevent protentional violent crimes such as armed robberies and shootings.   Officers encountered a group of known and unknown XXXassociates in which among them was XXX in the area of Roxbury Street and Washington St. Officers were very familiar with XXXfrom numerous encounters to which XXXwill walk over to officers and engage in a friendly conversation. On this day XXXappeared to not want to engage in any conversation. Officers were also aware that XXXwas recently shot at in the mission hill area. XXXwas with 3 other juvenile males in which they became vigilant of officers. XXXbegan to roll up and then proceed to light a marijuana joint. Officers were aware XXXwas only 13 years old in which he cannot legally possess marijuana. Officers exited their cruiser in an effort to converse with XXXand the group about the marijuana when then began to start to spread out in different directions. XXXXXXthen began to run away from officers while on Roxbury street clutching their waist band area.   Officers were able to follow behind and eventually stop all three but in different locations. At one point Officer Monzon was alone with XXXwhich he has detained and attempting to frisk when XXXcame up on him and ignored commands to stay back and not to interfere. XXXkept ignoring Officers commands and proceed to step to Officer Monzon in a bladed stance with balled up fists down by his side. Officer Monzon felt his safety was in jeopardy especially when he had reason to believe XXXwas potentially armed with a